Police have been unable to catch those who have been targeting homes and schools by spraying victims with a gas that leaves them unconscious. It is not clear what gas is being used in the attacks. Lungu was filmed on Tuesday telling a group of women that: "I'm making an earnest appeal to the people that are behind this gassing - to an extent of gassing innocent schoolchildren, innocent families. It is indeed a shame," Lungu was filmed on Tuesday telling a group of women. She then broke down in tears. --bbc--